<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-BKN-LAKERNOTES-LADN </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
FOX, HARPER BACK IN MIX
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By HOWARD BECK  
 c.1999 Los Angeles Daily News  
<TEXT>
<P>
   SAN ANTONIO _ Rick Fox returned from the infirmary and Derek
Harper returned from an involuntary extended breather Saturday, but
both key Los Angeles Lakers veterans were far from returning to
peak performances.
</P>
<P>
   Fox, out three games with a sore right knee, played 17 minutes,
making 2 of 6 shots for four points and two rebounds. Harper,
benched for four straight games and most of a fifth because coach
Kurt Rambis felt he needed rest, played 19 minutes and scored two
points.
</P>
<P>
   ``I liked what I saw in Harp,'' Rambis said. ``He brought a lot
of energy and effort. Rick seemed to be testing it a little bit, a
little bit unsure, but that's the nature of coming back from an
injury. There's a psychological barrier to break through because
you have to deal with the pain.''
</P>
<P>
   Nothing was more painful for Harper than going from starter to
48-minute bench warmer, a rarity in his 16 years in the league. He
never felt he needed the rest and said the time off probably hurt
more than helped at this point, disrupting his rhythm.
</P>
<P>
   ``I won't lie to you _ I don't have any rhythm,'' he said. ``I
haven't played for (10 days).''
</P>
<P>
   As for his health, which was Rambis' concern, Harper said: ``I
feel fine. It's not about me, though. If Fish (Derek Fisher) and Ty
(Lue) can get it done, so be it. But you wanna play, and you're
competitive. Whoever goes out there, we've got to find a way to get
it done.''
</P>
<P>
   Rambis still hasn't committed to any of his three point guards
as the starter for the playoffs, which begin in two weeks. He felt
it was time to get Harper, the steadiest of the trio, back in the
rotation.
</P>
<P>
   ``He showed me the other day in practice that his step is back,
he's spryer now than he was,'' Rambis said. The starting job ``is
not completely settled, but I always like what (Harper) did against
the starters for the most part whenever he was fresh, and Fish
coming off the bench and Ty being a speciality kind of guy. But
it's all subject to how we're playing and what we're doing.''
</P>
<P>
   Healed: Fox, his hair slicked back Mafia-style before the game,
joked that his 'do was a tribute to trainer Gary Vitti.
</P>
<P>
   ``The Italian trainer put me back on the court, so I slicked my
hair back in honor of him to thank him for once again repairing my
injuries,'' Fox quipped.
</P>
<P>
   Jokes aside, the Lakers needed Fox back. Kobe Bryant was logging
40-plus minutes without Fox to spell him and with only rookie Ruben
Patterson available as a sub. Fox also had been on a hot streak
before the injury _ averaging 11.9 points in his previous 10 games,
including 19- and 24-point outings against Utah.
</P>
<P>
   ``Rick gives us a nice punch off the bench, and it's good to be
able to bring him in and get some time,'' Rambis said.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
