<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-GEN-VOLLEYBALL-LONGBEACH-LADN </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
LONG BEACH STATE BEATS UC IRVINE
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By PAMELA LEWIS  
 Long Beach Press-Telegram  
<TEXT>
<P>
   LONG BEACH, Calif. _ This time Long Beach State left nothing to
groan about later.
</P>
<P>
   The second-ranked 49ers were fired up, showing enthusiasm on
every kill, ace, or dig, as they repaid UC Irvine an old debt,
15-7, 15-10, 15-6, in front of 1,409 in the first-round volleyball
match of the Mountain Pacific Sports Federation Tournament at the
Pyramid Saturday night.
</P>
<P>
   The 49ers advanced to the semifinals to play USC at 4 p.m.
Thursday in Provo, Utah. The Trojans beat Pepperdine Saturday,
15-7, 11-15, 15-9, 15-6.
</P>
<P>
   Top-ranked Brigham Young swept Pacific to host the semifinal and
final rounds, the latter scheduled for next Saturday.
</P>
<P>
   Dave McKienzie led Long Beach with 25 kills, Jim Polster had 17
kills plus eight digs and five blocks, and Matt Prosser had 12
kills and eight blocks.
</P>
<P>
   The 49ers hit .361 and held the 10th-ranked Anteaters to a .174
attack.
</P>
<P>
   It was a much different match than three weeks ago when UCI hit
.480 to upset the 49ers, who at the time were enjoying their first
No. 1 ranking since 1992.
</P>
<P>
   But Long Beach reduced its service errors from 27 to 12 and
outdug UCI, 38-23, this time.
</P>
<P>
   ``They came out and did what we talked about doing all week
long,'' Long Beach coach Ray Ratelle said. ``Certainly the biggest
difference was our serving. We served strategically and it worked
well.''
</P>
<P>
   The 49ers, who improved to 21-2, took control early in Game 1,
and were able to keep the Anteaters at bay.
</P>
<P>
   ``We knew that this is the playoff,'' said Curtis Jackson. ``We
can't hold anything back. We were all embarrassed after the first
match. We came out and we really wanted to prove something.''
</P>
<P>
   Long Beach trailed 4-0 in Game 2, but rallied to take the lead,
7-6, on a back row kill by McKienzie.
</P>
<P>
   The 49ers opened the third game 4-0 and UC Irvine never really
threatened.
</P>
<P>
   McKienzie had 10 kills apiece in the first two games.
</P>
<P>
   ``We definitely weren't losing tonight,'' he said. ``We were
coming out of this gym with a win tonight.''
</P>
<P>
   The win was the 12th in a row at the Pyramid this season for the
49ers, who finished undefeated at home for the first time since
1992.
</P>
<P>
   The 49ers showed more emotion and confidence than in any match
since they defeated top-ranked BYU.
</P>
<P>
   ``That's what we've been lacking,'' Prosser said. ``We've been
playing tentative in matches and we didn't do that tonight.''
</P>
<P>
   Donnie Rafter, who led UCI with 26 kills in the first meeting,
was held to five on 24 attempts. Erick Helenihi paced the Anteaters
(14-11) with 12 kills.
</P>
<P>
   Long Beach State also got 62 assists from Chris Seiffert, and
seven kills and a team-high 11 digs from Jackson.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
