<HEADER>
A2366 &Cx1f; tic-z
r s &Cx13;  &Cx11;  BC-FBN-ELWAY-BRONCOS-AZR     04-25 0529
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-FBN-ELWAY-BRONCOS-AZR </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
BRISTER AWAITS CHANCE TO VALIDATE FAITH SHOWN BY BRONCOS 
</HEADLINE>
   (For use by N.Y. Times News Service clients)  
 By STEVE SCHOENFELD  
 c.1999 The Arizona Republic  
<TEXT>
<P>
   John Elway's successor was so bad in the mid-1990s that he was
out of the NFL for one year.
</P>
<P>
   No team wanted Bubby Brister, who sat out the 1996 season.
</P>
<P>
   Finally, Denver Broncos linebacker Bill Romanowski, who had
played with Brister at Philadelphia in 1994, convinced Broncos
Coach Mike Shanahan to sign him.
</P>
<P>
   Three years later, Brister will be asked to take over a job held
by Elway since 1983.
</P>
<P>
   ``It's going to be more pressure than I've ever had and probably
would have ever dreamed of having,'' Brister said.
</P>
<P>
   Think things have changed for the Broncos, back-to-back Super
Bowl champions, and the rest of the AFC West?
</P>
<P>
   Next season, the starting quarterbacks in the division will be
Jon Kitna in Seattle, Rich Gannon in Oakland, Jim Harbaugh or Ryan
Leaf in San Diego, Elvis Grbac in Kansas City and Brister, 36, in
Denver.
</P>
<P>
   Just a few years ago, Jeff George was in Oakland, Stan Humphries
in San Diego, Rick Mirer in Seattle, Joe Montana in Kansas City and
Elway in Denver.
</P>
<P>
   ``You won't replace John Elway,'' said Bob Ferguson, vice
president of player personnel for the Cardinals, who left the
Broncos in 1996.
</P>
<P>
   ``But I think Mike (Shanahan) has been preparing for this _ the
drafting of Brian Griese and Jeff Lewis before him. Plus, Bubby has
proven to be successful. It shows how great that scheme (West Coast
offense) really is.''
</P>
<P>
   Last season, the Broncos were 5-0 in games Brister started for
an injured Elway.
</P>
<P>
   Brister's numbers were better than Elway's in those starts. He
completed 59.5 percent of his passes for 986 yards and 10
touchdowns. He was intercepted only three times and had a 99.0
passing rating.
</P>
<P>
   He will begin the preseason as a starter, with Griese, a
third-round pick a year ago, being groomed for the job. In
addition, the Broncos are expected to sign veteran Chris Miller,
who has been out of football since 1995.
</P>
<P>
   Lewis, the Horizon High School and Northern Arizona graduate,
was traded to Carolina in the off-season.
</P>
<P>
   Early in his career, Brister was known for being a hothead and
outspoken.
</P>
<P>
   He lost his starting job in Pittsburgh in 1992 when Bill Cowher
replaced Coach Chuck Noll. Then he was traded to Philadelphia after
criticizing starter Neil O'Donnell in the media. Brister said he
could ``outrun and out-throw'' O'Donnell.
</P>
<P>
   In 1993, Brister started eight games for the Eagles. He was the
backup to Randall Cunningham there the next year.
</P>
<P>
   In '95, he signed with the New York Jets and started only two
games, one in which he made all of the blooper highlight films. His
shovel pass was intercepted and returned for a touchdown by
Carolina inside linebacker Sam Mills.
</P>
<P>
   Brister's career was resuscitated by Shanahan and the Broncos a
year ago.
</P>
<P>
   ``By no means am I John Elway,'' Brister said. ``I just think if
I can fill my own shoes, that will be good enough for us to get
where we want to go.'' &QL; 
The Denver Post and Denver Rocky Mountain News contributed to this
article. &QL;
</P>
</TEXT>
