estimates in reporting its sixth consecutive profitable quarter. By
John Markoff.
</P>
<P>
   ATT-CABLETV-ANALYSIS (Undated) _ Just when it looked like AT&AMP;T
had settled down to manage its own $31.8 billion acquisition of
Tele-Communications Inc., the No. 2 cable carrier, the company made
an unsolicited bid to buy Mediaone for $58 billion. If the bid is
successful, AT&AMP;T would become the nation's No. 1 cable television
company, in addition to the nation's No. 1 long-distance telephone
carrier. By Seth Schiesel.
</P>
