   INTERNET-GOVERNMENT (Mountain View, Calif.) _ As the worlds of
politics and high technology increasingly come together, Virginia
Governor James S. Gilmore III is a man who would like to be at the
nexus. In recent years, Virginia's high-technology economy has
surged and Gilmore has made Internet policy central to his 18-month
stint in office. Now he is seeking to parlay his efforts into a
national role. By Matt Richtel.
</P>
<P>
   SUN-MICROSYSTEMS-SOFTWARE (San Francisco) _ Sun Microsystems
Inc. plans to introduce a software product on Monday that is
designed for companies that want to let their employees use various
devices to connect to corporate computer networks, secure from
unauthorized access. By John Markoff.
