</P>
<P>
   SCHOOL-MEMORIAL _ LITTLETON, Colo. _ On the first Sunday
following one of the deadliest school shootings in U.S. history,
this devastated city is holding an open-air memorial service to
rebuild its spirit of community and mourn its dead. Authorities
expect 35,000 people in a movie theater parking lot. Vice President
Gore, state officials and Christian singer Amy Grant are expected.
(MWilliams, Atlanta Journal-Constitution)
</P>
<P>
   ROGER-DEATH _ DAYTON, Ohio _ Funk artist Roger Troutman was
killed over the weekend. Police suspect his brother, who died
shortly after, apparently by shooting himself. (Dayton Daily News)
</P>
