<SLUG> BC-GEN-OFFBEAT-COLUMN-LADN-(SLANG) </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
CAST YOUR VOTE FOR WORLD'D DUMBEST SOUVENIR
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By TOM HOFFARTH  
 c.1999 Los Angeles Daily News  
<TEXT>
<P>
   No question, Michael Jordan had a great supporting cast when he
was with the Chicago Bulls.
</P>
<P>
   So . . . wanna own it?
</P>
<P>
   For a minimum bid of $2,000 (unfortunately likely to go much
higher), Mastro Fine Sports Auctions has the actual, grimy
heel-to-knee fiberglass cast that Jordan used to help heal a broken
foot in 1985, his second NBA season.
</P>
<P>
   You need proof it belonged to His Airness? Lot No. 172 also
includes medical records to ``prove beyond a doubt'' that ``our
consignor was there that day'' in the doctor's office when Jordan
had the cast removed. Jordan not only gave it away but also signed
it, according to the description of the piece in the auction's
catalogue.
</P>
<P>
   At the semi-regular sports memorabilia auction Thursday and
Friday out of Oak Brook, Ill., there's the usual game-worn fare of
expensive trinkets.
</P>
<P>
   Among the 1,500 items are personal treasures you hate to see up
for auction, such as Mike Cuellar's 1969 American League Cy Young
Award trophy or the bat Mark McGwire used to hit his first
professional home run in 1984 with the Single-A Modesto A's.
</P>
<P>
   There's some neat Hall of Fame-type items like a Red Grange
leather helmet (minimum bid $10,000), Gordie Howe's size 102/3
skates ($750) and a Babe Ruth Louisville Slugger with eight notches
near the label that represent the homers he hit with that bat
($15,000).
</P>
<P>
   Then there's stuff like Jordan's cast, as well as:
</P>
<P>
   __ No. 173: Jordan's expired 1991 Illinois drivers license. With
lots of staple holes where the state troopers attached violations.
Minimum bid: $1,000.
</P>
<P>
   __ No. 237: Tonya Harding's purple sequined costume, worn when
she won the 1994 U.S. Figure Skating Championship _ when Nancy
Kerrigan was forced to pull out after an unfortunate knee injury.
Minimum bid: $2,000.
</P>
<P>
   __ No. 654: A mint-condition (no bullet holes or alcohol stains)
long maroon robe trimmed in black with a ``TRC'' monogram that Ty
Cobb wore when Al Stump visited his house to write his biography.
Minimum bid: $900.
</P>
<P>
   __ No. 714: A passport Mickey Mantle used to visit Bermuda, the
Bahamas, Canada, the Dominican Republic and France from 1976 to
'81. Minimum bid: $6,000.
</P>
<P>
   __ No. 732: The rosin bag Montreal pitchers used on Sept. 27,
1998, when McGwire hit homers No. 69 and 70. Minimum bid: $900.
</P>
<P>
   More information on the auction is available via the Internet
(www.auctioninc.com or at www.mastrofsa.com) or by phone: (630)
472-9551.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
