<DOCTYPE> NEWS STORY </DOCTYPE>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-04-25 19:39 </DATE_TIME>
<HEADER>
A2572 &Cx1f; tth-z
u e &Cx13;  &Cx11;  BC-SUMMER-LIST-SPI &LR;      04-25 1374
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-SUMMER-LIST-SPI </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
SUMMER MOVIE RELEASES FOR 1999 
</HEADLINE>
   (For use by New York Times News Service clients.)  
 By WILLIAM ARNOLD  
 c.1999 Seattle Post-Intelligencer  
<TEXT>
<P>
   The following is Hollywood's summer '99 release schedule as it
now stands. But expect the usual second-guessing, repositioning and
week-by-week changes.
</P>
<P>
   MAY 19
</P>
<P>
   Star Wars: Episode I _ The Phantom Menace _ George Lucas'
prequel to his ``Star Wars Trilogy,'' and the most eagerly awaited,
most-hyped movie in history.
</P>
<P>
   MAY 21
</P>
<P>
   The Love Letter _ Kate Capshaw and Tom Selleck head the cast of
this DreamWorks comedy about an unsigned love letter that wakes up
a sleepy New England town.
</P>
<P>
   Endurance _ A documentary about the Ethiopian runner who stole
the spotlight of the 1996 Olympics.
</P>
<P>
   Lovers of the Arctic Circle _ A Spanish love story about ``two
young lovers drawn together by the sheer force of fate.''
</P>
<P>
   MAY 28
</P>
<P>
   Notting Hill _ A comedy about a romance between a small
bookstore owner (Hugh Grant) and the biggest movie star in the
world (Julia Roberts).
</P>
<P>
   American Pie _ A gross-out comedy about a group of friends ``who
make a pact to lose their virginity by prom night.''
</P>
<P>
   13th Floor _ A thriller about a virtual reality technology that
``creates a living, breathing simulation of 1937 Los Angeles on a
computer chip.''
</P>
<P>
   JUNE 4
</P>
<P>
   Limbo _ The new John Sayles film, a drama set in the ``rugged
islands of Southeastern Alaska.''
</P>
<P>
   Instinct _ Anthony Hopkins and Cuba Gooding Jr. star in a
thriller about a mysterious prisoner held for murder in the jungles
of Central Africa.
</P>
<P>
   Buena Vista Social Club _ A Wim Wenders-directed music
documentary, with Ry Cooder and some of Cuba's greatest musicians.
</P>
<P>
   My Son the Fanatic _ Rachel Griffiths, Om Puri and Stellan
Skarsgard star in a culture-clash love story from the writer of
``My Beautiful Laundrette.''
</P>
<P>
   JUNE 11
</P>
<P>
   Austin Powers: The Spy Who Shagged Me _ This Mike Myers
follow-up to his 1997 James Bond sendup is the summer's second most
eagerly awaited sequel.
</P>
<P>
   The General's Daughter _ John Travolta stars in a murder mystery
set on a U.S. Army post.
</P>
<P>
   My Life So Far _ The ``Chariots of Fire'' team of producer David
Puttnam and director Hugh Hudson reunite for this coming-of-age
comedy-drama.
</P>
<P>
   JUNE 18
</P>
<P>
   The Thomas Crowne Affair _ John McTiernan's remake of the 1968
Norman Jewison hit, with Pierce Brosnan in the Steve McQueen role.
</P>
<P>
   Tarzan _ Phil Collins wrote the music for the summer's Disney
animated musical, the movies' umpteenth version of the Edgar Rice
Burroughs' classic.
</P>
<P>
   South Park: Bigger, Longer &AMP; Uncut _ A big-screen version of the
bad-taste animated television show.
</P>
<P>
   JUNE 25
</P>
<P>
   Big Daddy _ The summer's Adam Sandler comedy, about an immature
young man who adopts a 5-year-old to impress his girlfriend.
</P>
<P>
   An Ideal Husband _ An adaptation of the Oscar Wilde play,
starring Cate Blanchett, Minnie Driver, Rupert Everett, Julianne
Moore and Jeremy Northam.
</P>
<P>
   JULY 2
</P>
<P>
   Wild, Wild West _ The big-screen version of the campy 1960s TV
western series, directed by Barry Sonnenfeld and starring Will
Smith and Kevin Kline.
</P>
<P>
   The Lovers On the Bridge _ Juliette Binoche stars in this French
love story about two runaways who meet on Paris' famed Pont-Neuf.
</P>
<P>
   JULY 9
</P>
<P>
   Princess Mononoke _ A Japanese animated fairy tale that is the
first film to ever break the $150 million level at the Japanese
box-office.
</P>
<P>
   Dick _ A '70s comedy about two teenagers who get swept up in the
Watergate scandal.
</P>
<P>
   Stigmata _ An ``Exorcist''-like thriller starring Patricia
Arquette as a young woman being investigated by the Vatican.
</P>
<P>
   JULY 16
</P>
<P>
   Eyes Wide Shut _ An erotic thriller starring Tom Cruise and
Nicole Kidman that is the long-awaited new film by the late Stanley
Kubrick.
</P>
<P>
   Lake Placid _ A David E. Kelley-written whodunit starring
Bridget Fonda as a New York paleontologist investigating a murder
at a remote lake in Maine.
</P>
<P>
   The Blair Witch Project _ A low-budget thriller about a trio of
Maryland filmmakers who disappear while filming a documentary about
a local phantom.
</P>
<P>
   JULY 23
</P>
<P>
   Bowfinger's Big Thing _ A comedy teaming Steve Martin and Eddie
Murphy as a wannabe producer and the world's top action star.
</P>
<P>
   Inspector Gadget _ Matthew Broderick plays the bionic detective
hero in this adaptation of the TV cartoon show.
</P>
<P>
   Haunting of Hill House _ Jan De Bont (``Twister,'' ``Speed'')
directed this remake of ``The Haunting'' starring Liam Neeson and
Catherine Zeta-Jones.
</P>
<P>
   JULY 30
</P>
<P>
   Summer of Sam _ Spike Lee's film about the ``Son of Sam'' murder
spree that terrified New York City in the summer of 1977.
</P>
<P>
   Outside Providence _ A coming-of-age comedy produced by the
Farrelly Brothers (``There's Something About Mary'') and starring
Shawn Hatosy and Alec Baldwin.
</P>
<P>
   Muppets From Space _ A search for Gonzo's past involves the
Muppets in this kiddie sci-fi adventure.
</P>
<P>
   Runaway Bride _ The director (Garry Marshall) and stars (Richard
Gere and Julia Roberts) of ``Pretty Woman'' team up for another
romantic comedy.
</P>
<P>
   Deep Blue Sea _ A Renny Harlin-directed thriller about a group
of marine researchers menaced by genetically altered sharks.
</P>
<P>
   Drop Dead Gorgeous _ A beauty pageant comedy starring Kirstie
Alley and Ellen Barkin as the mothers of two rival contestants.
</P>
<P>
   AUG. 6
</P>
<P>
   The Fight Club _ Brad Pitt and Edward Norton star in this drama
about an organization that hosts bloody, no-holds-barred gladiator
bouts.
</P>
<P>
   Plunkett and McLean _ Robert Caryle and Johnny Lee Miller play
18th-century highwaymen who infiltrate high society.
</P>
<P>
   Mystery Men _ An action-comedy adaptation of the Dark Horse
comic starring Ben Stiller, Hank Azaria and William H. Macy.
</P>
<P>
   The Iron Giant _ An animated feature about the friendship
between a small boy and a giant metal machine that falls to Earth
from outer space.
</P>
<P>
   AUG. 11
</P>
<P>
   Next to You _ A high school romantic comedy based on the novel,
``Girl Gives Birth to Own Prom Date,'' starring Melissa Joan Hart
and Adrian Grenier.
</P>
<P>
   AUG. 13
</P>
<P>
   Mickey Blue Eyes _ An ``Analyze This''-like comedy starring Hugh
Grant as an English art dealer who falls in love with the daughter
of a Mafia don.
</P>
<P>
   The 13th Warrior _ The long-delayed film version of Michael
Crichton's Viking novel, ``Eaters of the Dead,'' starring Antonio
Banderas.
</P>
<P>
   Detroit Rock City _ A '70s nostalgia comedy about four teenagers
``who embark on a wild adventure to attend a KISS concert.''
</P>
<P>
   AUG. 20
</P>
<P>
   The Muse _ Albert Brooks directed and stars in this Hollywood
satire co-starring Sharon Stone and Jeff Bridges.
</P>
<P>
   Blue Streak _ A comedy starring Martin Lawrence as a thief
trying to retrieve diamonds he hid in a construction site that
became a police precinct.
</P>
<P>
   AUG. 27
</P>
<P>
   The Astronaut's Wife _ Johnny Depp and Charlize Theron in a
story modeled after the '50s sci-fi classic, ``I Married a Monster
From Outer Space.''
</P>
<P>
   Killing Mrs. Tingle _ A high school black comedy starring Helen
Mirren and directed by Kevin Williamson, the writer of ``Scream.''
</P>
<P>
   Mad about Mambo _ A comedy about an 18-year-old boy who takes
mambo lessons to improve his soccer skills and falls in love with
his instructor.
</P>
<P>
   SUMMER (no firm date)
</P>
<P>
   Hoofbeats _ An outdoor adventure with a mostly horse cast set in
1914 Southwest Africa.
</P>
<P>
   Universal Soldier: the Return _ A sequel to the 1992 sci-fi
action hit, with Jean-Claude Van Damme back as the cyborg hero.
</P>
<P>
   Mr. Accident _ A comedy from Australia's Yahoo Serious, about a
scheme to market nicotine-injected eggs.
</P>
<P>
   In Too Deep _ Omar Epps follows up his ``The Mod Squad'' role
playing another undercover cop in this inner city gangster thriller
co-starring LL Cool J.
</P>
<P>
   Alice et Martin _ A French drama about ``a young man haunted by
his past,'' directed by Andre Techine and starring Juliette Binoche
and Alexis Loret.
</P>
<P>
   Lucie Aubrac _ A big-budget, French-language romantic drama, set
in the French Resistance of World War II, directed by Claude Berri
and starring Carole Bouquet.
</P>
</TEXT>
