NATO leaders ended their summit meeting on Sunday with expressions
of solidarity in prevailing over President Slobodan Milosevic of
Yugoslavia and a group portrait. The three-day NATO summit,
originally called to celebrate the 50th anniversary of the alliance
was largely overshadowed by the crisis in Kosovo. (Stephen
Crowley/New York Times Photo)
