<P>
   (NYT7) KUKES, Albania -- April 25, 1999 -- KOSOVO-IMPACT, 4-25
-- Refugees from Kosovo took a moment of quiet by a lake on Sunday
in Kukes. The United Nations High Commissioner for Refugees
estimates that there are about 363,100 in Albania, 135,200 in
Macedonia, 65,700 in Montenegro, and 32,500 in Bosnia and
Herzegovina. More than 15,000 have been evacuated from Macedonia to
13 countries, the agency said, including nearly 10,000 to Germany.
(Edward Keating/New York Times Photo)
</P>
<P>
   (NYT6) SPRINGFIELD, Va. -- April 25, 1999 -- , 4-25 --
GUN-GROUP-PRATT, 4-25 -- Larry Pratt, the executive director of the
Gun Owners of America, an advocacy group situated in Springfield,
Va. Pratt believes there should be absolutely no regulations
governing the sale or purchase of handguns and automatic weapons.
In this more perfect world, Pratt says, many of the deaths in
Colorado might have been prevented. ``We're saddened that there
were not teachers and principals who had access to a gun, who might
have been able to stop the mayhem,'' says Pratt. (Scott
Robinson/New York Times Photo)
</P>
<P>
   (NYT5) ENNIS, Mont. -- April 25, 1999 -- WILDERNESS-ACCESS, 4-25
-- Bruce Combs and his family nearly lost access to government land
from their Montana dude ranch. A new neighbor had threatened to
block the family's access to the land, resulting in a lawsuit. It
is the sort of dispute that has become increasingly common in the
West as wealthy people from out of state buy land that includes
roads and trails long used by the natives. The Combses have been
entertaining guests in and around their dude ranch in Jack Creek
Canyon since 1959. (Jim Robbins/New York Times Photo)
</P>
<P>
   (NYT4) TIRANA, Albania -- April 25, 1999 --
SUB-KOSOVO-MILITARY-2, 4-24 -- The NATO supreme military commander,
