4-24 -- Apache attack helicopters arriving in Albania on Sunday.
While denying plans for ground troops, NATO intends to strike more
closely at Serb units on the ground with the low-flying Apaches,
now deployed in Albania and being prepared for use. The NATO
supreme military commander, Gen. Wesley Clark, says that the allied
campaign against the Serbs is ``right on schedule.'' (James
Hill/New York Times Photo)
